aWPnC_OfferedService.Description: {\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deflang1033{\fonttbl{\f0\fswiss\fprq2\fcharset0 MS Sans Serif;}{\f1\froman\fprq2\fcharset2 Symbol;}{\f2\fmodern\fprq1\fcharset0 Courier New;}{\f3\fnil\fprq2\fcharset2 Wingdings;}{\f4\fnil\fcharset0 MS Sans Serif;}} {\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;} \viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\f0\fs16 Coverage A only covers the physical structure of the dwelling and not any other structures such as guest house, fences, detatched garage etc. It does however cover an attached garage, meaning the structure is physically tied to the home and by wall and roof. A build in type garage is also covered, but it differs because the garage is bordered to the top by living area of the home.\par \par For information: limit and deductible are per occurence\par In this example:\par \pard\fi-360\li720\f1\'b7\tab\f0 Dwelling coverage $10,000\par \f1\'b7\tab\f0 Deductible $500\par \f1\'b7\tab\f0 Claim\par \pard\fi-360\li1440\f2 o\tab\f0 Roof damage = $5,000\par \f2 o\tab\f0 Exterior walls damage = $7,000\par \f2 o\tab\f0 Total claim $12,000\par \f2 o\tab\f0 Payment:\par \pard\fi-360\li2160\f3\'a7\tab\f0 $12,000 minus $500 deductible = $11,500 (The deductible doesn\rquote t apply per benefit, but only one under the coverage: Each occurrence for dwelling coverage)\par \f3\'a7\tab\f0 But insured only has a $10,000 limit\par \f3\'a7\tab\f0 Company pays $10,000\par \pard\f4\par }

aWFRuleDesc.RuleDescription:
To set up a deductible per occurence: a deductible per delivered service must be setup + a deductible per claim folder (which represents the limit of deductible that can be applied). At claim time the claim specialist can split the deductible on the delivered services if he wants to. Here the deductible per occurence is equal to the deductible per delivered service and is not chosen at subscription.
Deductible will be applied 'per each occurrence' on the coverage, not per the benefit. For example: During a wind storm if the following were damaged: roof & exterior walls. If the insured had a $500 deductible, the total claim payout would be less the $500 deductible.

aWFRuleDesc.RuleDescription:
If 100% multiply dwelling premium by 10% If 125% by 15% If 150% by 20% If 175% by 25% If 200% by 30%
Rule is executed for each item
aWFRuleDesc.RuleText:
; aWF_RT_Formule (aWPnC_ItemRuleEngine) (Def Version:3) (Implem Version:1)
uses WFTypes
type tWF___PercentageofDwellingLimit : (_100_, _125_, _150_, _175_, _200_)
function Option__Dynamic_Data__PercentageofDwellingLimit return tWF___PercentageofDwellingLimit type tpValue : .tWF___PercentageofDwellingLimit
var p : tWF___PercentageofDwellingLimit
if self.EvaluateFieldDescFromRank(0, 5, 'Option__Dynamic_Data__PercentageofDwellingLimit') p = tpValue(self.pFieldValue). _Result = p endIf endFunc
procedure Set_Option__Dynamic_Data__PercentageofDwellingLimit(_DataValue : tWF___PercentageofDwellingLimit) self.SetDynDataValue('Percentage of Dwelling Limit', @_DataValue) endProc
procedure WFCalculate(inOut Result : tWFNum8) if self.Option__Dynamic_Data__PercentageofDwellingLimit = _100_ Result = self.PremiumRate('Cov A') * 0.1 elseif self.Option__Dynamic_Data__PercentageofDwellingLimit = _125_ Result = self.PremiumRate('Cov A') * 0.15 elseif self.Option__Dynamic_Data__PercentageofDwellingLimit = _150_ Result = self.PremiumRate('Cov A') * 0.2 elseif self.Option__Dynamic_Data__PercentageofDwellingLimit = _175_ Result = self.PremiumRate('Cov A') * 0.25 elseif self.Option__Dynamic_Data__PercentageofDwellingLimit = _200_ Result = self.PremiumRate('Cov A') * 0.3 endIf endProc
aWFRuleDesc.Name: Guaranteed Replacement Cost Rate

aWFRuleDesc.RuleDescription: Replacement cost limit is a percentage amount of the dwelling limit: Limit/Percent Amount: -100% -125% (default) -150% -175% -200%
aWFRuleDesc.RuleText:
; aWF_RT_Formule (aWPnC_ItemRuleEngine) (Def Version:2) (Implem Version:1)
uses WFTypes
type tWF___PercentageofDwellingLimit : (_100_, _125_, _150_, _175_, _200_)
function Option__Dynamic_Data__PercentageofDwellingLimit return tWF___PercentageofDwellingLimit type tpValue : .tWF___PercentageofDwellingLimit
var p : tWF___PercentageofDwellingLimit
if self.EvaluateFieldDescFromRank(0, 5, 'Option__Dynamic_Data__PercentageofDwellingLimit') p = tpValue(self.pFieldValue). _Result = p endIf endFunc
procedure Set_Option__Dynamic_Data__PercentageofDwellingLimit(_DataValue : tWF___PercentageofDwellingLimit) self.SetDynDataValue('Percentage of Dwelling Limit', @_DataValue) endProc
procedure WFCalculate(inOut Result : tWFNum8) var dwellingLimit : Num8
dwellingLimit = self.Contract__ItemLimitValueOfCoverage('Cov A Dwelling Limit', 'Cov A') if self.Option__Dynamic_Data__PercentageofDwellingLimit = _100_ Result = dwellingLimit elseif self.Option__Dynamic_Data__PercentageofDwellingLimit = _125_ Result = dwellingLimit * 1.25 elseif self.Option__Dynamic_Data__PercentageofDwellingLimit = _150_ Result = dwellingLimit * 1.5 elseif self.Option__Dynamic_Data__PercentageofDwellingLimit = _175_ Result = dwellingLimit * 1.75 elseif self.Option__Dynamic_Data__PercentageofDwellingLimit = _200_ Result = dwellingLimit * 2 endIf endProc
aWFRuleDesc.Name: Limit

aWPnC_OfferedService.Name: Guaranteed Replacement Cost
